          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">
            Contemporary Relevance
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            In today's fast-paced world, the Mandala Krama offers a timeless
            method for finding inner peace and expanding awareness. Modern
            psychologists, including Carl Jung, have recognized the therapeutic
            value of mandalas in psychological integration and wholeness.
          </p>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-6 italic text-gray-600 mb-8">
            "The mandala is an archetypal image whose occurrence is attested
            throughout the ages. It signifies the wholeness of the Self." — Carl
            Jung
          </div>

          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
            Whether approached as a spiritual practice, artistic expression, or
            psychological tool, the Mandala Krama continues to offer profound
            insights into the nature of consciousness and our place in the
            cosmos.
          </p>
        </div>

